    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing return statement in ESM message encoding error path\n\n### Summary\nThe ESM message encoding function `esm_msg_encode` was missing a return statement in its error handling path. When message encoding failed, the function would log the error but continue execution instead of immediately returning the error code. This could lead to incorrect behavior downstream.\n\nThe issue was identified during code review comparing error handling patterns between encode and decode functions. The decode function properly returned on error, but the encode function did not.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/esm_msg.c`: Added missing `LOG_FUNC_RETURN(encode_result);` in error handling block of `esm_msg_encode` function.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions where ESM message encoding fails (e.g., buffer too short, unsupported message type), the function would not properly propagate the error code to calling functions. This could result in:\n- Incorrect message lengths being reported\n- Attempted transmission of partially encoded messages\n- Potential memory corruption if negative return values were misinterpreted\n\nThe issue is most likely to manifest when the UE or MME attempts to encode ESM messages with invalid parameters or insufficient buffer space.\n"
}